#include "gxdlcode.h"

#if defined (__USE_NATIVE_INT_TYPES__)
int main() { return 0; } // No test for native types
#else
#if defined (__64_BIT_DATABASE_ENGINE__)

#if defined (__USE_ANSI_CPP__) // Use the ANSI Standard C++ library
#include <iostream>
using namespace std; // Use unqualified names for Standard C++ library
#else // Use the old iostream library by default
#include <iostream.h>
#endif // __USE_ANSI_CPP__

#include "gxuint64.h"

#if defined (__MSVC__)
#pragma warning(disable:4244) // Function template instantiation warning
#endif

// Positive and Negative limits Constants 
#if defined (__WIN32__)
const __LLWORD__   LLWORDPositiveLimit = 9223372036854775807;
const __LLWORD__   LLWORDNegitiveLimit = 9223372036854775808;
const __ULLWORD__  ULLWORDLimit        = 18446744073709551615;
#elif defined (__UNIX__)
const __LLWORD__   LLWORDPositiveLimit = 9223372036854775807LL;
const __LLWORD__   LLWORDNegitiveLimit = 9223372036854775808LL;
const __ULLWORD__  ULLWORDLimit        = 18446744073709551615LL;
#else
#error You must define a target platform: __WIN32__ or __UNIX__
#endif

void PausePrg()
{
  cout << "\n";
  cout << "Press enter to continue..." << "\n";
  cin.get();
}

void ClearInputStream(istream &s)
// Used to clear istream
{
  char c;
  s.clear();
  while(s.get(c) && c != '\n') { ; }
}

template<class TYPEX, class TYPEY>
inline void OperatorTest(TYPEX x, TYPEY y)
{
  char *tf[2] = {"FALSE", "TRUE"};
  cout << "\n";

  cout << "Value x = " << x << ", Value y = " << y << "\n";
  TYPEX z;
  cout << x << " += " << y << " = "; z = x; z += y; cout << z << "\n";
  cout << x << " -= " << y << " = "; z = x; z -= y; cout << z << "\n";
  cout << x << " *= " << y << " = "; z = x; z *= y; cout << z << "\n";
  cout << x << " /= " << y << " = "; z = x; z /= y; cout << z << "\n";
  cout << x << " * " << y << " = " ; z = (x * y); cout << z << "\n";
  cout << x << " / " << y << " = " ; z = (x / y); cout << z << "\n";
  cout << x << " + " << y << " = " ; z = (x + y); cout << z << "\n";
  cout << x << " - " << y << " = " ; z = (x - y); cout << z << "\n";
  cout << x << " == " << y << " = " << tf[(x == y)] << "\n";
  cout << x << " != " << y << " = " << tf[(x != y)] << "\n";
  cout << x << " <= " << y << " = " << tf[(x <= y)] << "\n";
  cout << x << " >= " << y << " = " << tf[(x >= y)] << "\n";
  cout << x << " < " << y << " = " << tf[(x < y)] << "\n";
  cout << x << " > " << y << " = " << tf[(x > y)] << "\n";
  cout << x << "++ = "; z = x; z++; cout << z << "\n";
  cout << x << "-- = "; z = x; z--; cout << z << "\n"; 
  cout << "++" << x << " = "; z = x; ++z; cout << z << "\n";
  cout << "--" << x << " = "; z = x; --z; cout << z << "\n";
}
#endif // __64_BIT_DATABASE_ENGINE__

int main()
{
#if defined (__64_BIT_DATABASE_ENGINE__)

  gxUINT64 a = LLWORDPositiveLimit;
  gxUINT64 b(LLWORDNegitiveLimit);
  gxUINT64 c;
  c = ULLWORDLimit;
  cout << "gxUINT64 unsigned limit: " << c << "\n";

  PausePrg();
  
  cout << "Testing gxUINT64 copy constructor..." << "\n";
  gxUINT64 d(a);
  cout << d << "\n";

  cout << "\n";
  cout << "Testing gxUINT64 assignment operator..." << "\n";
  gxUINT64 e;
  e = a;
  cout << e << "\n";

  PausePrg();

  cout << "Testing overloaded operators (gxUINT64, gxUINT64)..." << "\n";
  gxUINT64 buf1, buf2, al, bl;
  
  cout << "Enter first integer: ";
  cin >> buf1;
  if(cin) {
    a = buf1;
    al = buf1;
    cout << "Enter second integer: ";
    cin >> buf2;
  }
  else {
    cout << "Input stream broken. Exiting..." << "\n";
    return 0;
  }
  if(cin) {
    b = buf2;
    bl = buf2;
  }
  else {
    cout << "Input stream broken. Exiting..." << "\n";
    return 0;
  }

  ClearInputStream(cin);
    
  cout << "\n";
  
  OperatorTest(a, b);

  PausePrg();

  cout << "Testing overloaded operators (gxUINT64, __LWORD__)..." << "\n";
  OperatorTest(a, bl); 

  PausePrg();

  cout << "Testing overloaded operators (__LWORD__, gxUINT64)..." << "\n";
  OperatorTest(al, b);
  
  PausePrg();

  cout << "Testing overloaded operators (gxUINT64, __WORD__)..." << "\n";
  OperatorTest(a, (__WORD__)bl);

  PausePrg();

  cout << "Testing overloaded operators (__WORD__, gxUINT64)..." << "\n";
  OperatorTest((__WORD__)al, b);

  PausePrg();

  cout << "Testing overloaded operators (gxUINT64, __SWORD__)..." << "\n";
  OperatorTest(a, (__SWORD__)bl);

  PausePrg();

  cout << "Testing overloaded operators (__SWORD__, gxUINT64)..." << "\n";
  OperatorTest((__SWORD__)al, b);

  PausePrg();
  
  cout << "Testing overloaded operators (gxUINT64, __UWORD__)..." << "\n";
  OperatorTest(a, (__UWORD__)bl);

  PausePrg();

  cout << "Testing overloaded operators (__UWORD__, gxUINT64)..." << "\n";
  OperatorTest((__UWORD__)al, b);

  PausePrg();

  cout << "Testing overloaded operators (gxUINT64, __USWORD__)..." << "\n";
  OperatorTest(a, (__USWORD__)bl);

  PausePrg();

  cout << "Testing overloaded operators (__USWORD__, gxUINT64)..." << "\n";
  OperatorTest((__USWORD__)al, b);

  PausePrg();
  
  cout << "Testing overloaded operators (gxUINT64, __SBYTE__)..." << "\n";
  OperatorTest(a, 'B');

  PausePrg();

  cout << "Testing overloaded operators (__SBYTE__, gxUINT64)..." << "\n";
  OperatorTest('A', b);

#endif // __64_BIT_DATABASE_ENGINE__

  return 0;
}

#if defined (__MSVC__)
#pragma warning(default:4244) // Restore previous warning
#endif

#endif // __USE_NATIVE_INT_TYPES__
